><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_4097359\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_4097359\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Nov 12, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104zak1665702789358_2.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zak1665702789358_2.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zak1665702789358_2.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"zak1665702789358\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"zak1665702789358__menu_plug_in_structs_132381\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The Structs returned by <span class=\"keyword apiname\">getGlobalMenuOptions</span> and\n         <span class=\"keyword apiname\">getEditorMenuOptions</span> have a defined structure.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">A menu Struct has one or more option members, each containing the following members:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zak1665702789358__li_d21437e1_d21438e1_d21439e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">label</code>—text to display in the menu.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zak1665702789358__li_d21440e1_d21441e1_d21442e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">component</code>—name of the component that implements the callback\n            operation.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zak1665702789358__li_d21443e1_d21444e1_d21445e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">operation</code>—name of the callback operation to activate when the option is\n            clicked.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zak1665702789358__li_d21446e1_d21447e1_d21448e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">enabled</code>—a Boolean (with possible values\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code>|<code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code>) that indicates whether the option is enabled\n            or not, in which case it is dimmed.</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\">It is possible to specify a separator between menu options by defining a menu option with\n         only a label with the value _sep_. This separator is displayed only if another option\n         follows in the runtime menu. This ensures that if an option is not displayed (for example,\n         it is applicable to a different type of object), that no empty section is displayed. For\n         example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[menu]\n [option]\n [label] = \"Option 1\"\n [component] = \"MY_CPT\"\n [operation] = \"doOption1\"\n [enabled] = 1\n [option]\n [label] = \"_sep_\"\n [option]\n [label] = \"Option 2\"\n [component] = \"MY_CPT\"\n [operation] = \"doOption2\"\n [enabled] = 0</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zak1665702789358__topic_d27332e1_d27333e1_d27334e1_d27335e1_d27336e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d721956e105\">\n                  \n Example: Building a menu option struct\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zak1665702789358__p_d42746e1_d42747e1_d42748e1\">The following function builds the Struct for a single\n            user-defined menu option. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kec1718082865771.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kec1718082865771.html\" title=\"A Struct is a tree-like data structure in memory that is used to dynamically manipulate complex data and transform it from or to XML, JSON, or Uniface component data. A Struct can be addressed by assigning it to a variable, parameter, or non-database field of type struct, and manipulated using ProcScript commands, access operators, and information functions. For information on using Structs, see Transforming Complex Data Using Structs.\">Structs</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">function addOption\n params\n struct pMenu: in\n string pLabel: in\n string pComponentName: in\n string pCallbackOperation: in\n numeric pEnabled: in\n endparams\n variables\n struct vOption\n endvariables\n \n pMenu-&gt;option{-1} = $newstruct ;- add a new option\n vOption = pMenu-&gt;option{-1}\n vOption-&gt;label = pLabel\n vOption-&gt;component = pComponentName\n vOption-&gt;operation = pCallbackOperation\n vOption-&gt;enabled = pEnabled\n \n return 0\nend ;- function addOption</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zak1665702789358__p_d42749e1_d42750e1_d42751e1\">This can be called by the <span class=\"keyword apiname\">getGlobalMenuOptions</span> and <span class=\"keyword apiname\">getEditorMenuOptions</span> operations to build up menu Struct that may contain multiple user-defined options. For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">pMenu-&gt;$name = \"menu\"\ncall addOption(pMenu, \"Option 1\", \"MY_CPT\", \"doOption1\", 1)\ncall addOption(pMenu, \"Option 2\", \"MY_CPT\", \"doOption2\", 0)\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rgw1705580165965.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Define Keyboard Shortcuts for Menu Items</a><p>Menu definitions can define keyboard shortcuts that enable the user to select a menu item using the keyboard rather than the mouse. Keyboard shortcuts can be defined as an access key or an accelerator key.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_4097359\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_4097359\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Menu Plug-In Structs Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Nov 12, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 The Structs returned by getGlobalMenuOptions and getEditorMenuOptions have a defined structure. A menu Struct has one or more option members, each containing the following members: label —text to display in the menu. component —name of the component that implements the callback operation. operation —name of the callback operation to activate when the option is clicked. enabled —a Boolean (with possible values 1 | 0 ) that indicates whether the option is enabled or not, in which case it is dimmed. It is possible to specify a separator between menu options by defining a menu option with only a label with the value _sep_. This separator is displayed only if another option follows in the runtime menu. This ensures that if an option is not displayed (for example, it is applicable to a different type of object), that no empty section is displayed. For example: [menu] [option] [label] = \"Option 1\" [component] = \"MY_CPT\" [operation] = \"doOption1\" [enabled] = 1 [option] [label] = \"_sep_\" [option] [label] = \"Option 2\" [component] = \"MY_CPT\" [operation] = \"doOption2\" [enabled] = 0 Copy Example: Building a menu option struct The following function builds the Struct for a single user-defined menu option. For more information, see Structs . function addOption params struct pMenu: in string pLabel: in string pComponentName: in string pCallbackOperation: in numeric pEnabled: in endparams variables struct vOption endvariables pMenu->option{-1} = $newstruct ;- add a new option vOption = pMenu->option{-1} vOption->label = pLabel vOption->component = pComponentName vOption->operation = pCallbackOperation vOption->enabled = pEnabled return 0 end ;- function addOption Copy This can be called by the getGlobalMenuOptions and getEditorMenuOptions operations to build up menu Struct that may contain multiple user-defined options. For example: pMenu->$name = \"menu\" call addOption(pMenu, \"Option 1\", \"MY_CPT\", \"doOption1\", 1) call addOption(pMenu, \"Option 2\", \"MY_CPT\", \"doOption2\", 0) Copy Related Links Define Keyboard Shortcuts for Menu Items Menu definitions can define keyboard shortcuts that enable the user to select a menu item using the keyboard rather than the mouse. Keyboard shortcuts can be defined as an access key or an accelerator key. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}